external_knowledge:
- "Blossoming surveys" refers to surveys that are currently active;
- "Watered with active engagement" means the surveys have received at least one response;
- "Bear the fruits of feedback" refers to the various average scores collected from the survey responses.

- The `average_satisfaction` is an average score reflecting user satisfaction with the product;
- The `total_responses` represents the total number of user responses collected for each survey;
- The `product_id` of 1 is used to filter the results to a specific product.

- "top 5 surveys" refers to the surveys with the highest average satisfaction scores;
- "user satisfaction" is measured by the `average_satisfaction` score;
- "details" include the survey name, product name, average satisfaction, feedback text, and feedback date.

- "blossomed with more than one participant's completion" refers to surveys with more than one participant who completed the survey;
- "since the new year began" refers to the period starting from January 1, 2023;
- "feedback was given after the turn of the year" refers to feedback provided on or after January 1, 2023.

- 'stand tall as the crowning glory' refers to surveys with the highest average satisfaction score;
- 'blooming with the highest average satisfaction' refers to the maximum average_satisfaction in the analytics table;
- 'the stories behind them' include the survey_name and survey_description;
- 'the products they represent' include the product_name.

- "Gardeners" refer to users who have participated in the survey;
- "Tended to the survey's plot" means they have provided at least one response;
- "Watering the plants" is a metaphor for completing survey responses;
- "How long on average" refers to the average response duration.
